"""
Waymo Caption Checker v2 — FULL GRAMMAR + LOW CONFIDENCE + SLM
================================================================
Three-pass pipeline:
  Pass 1 — Rule-based Grammar (600+ rules, 25 categories)
  Pass 2 — Low Confidence Words (20 categories, 150+ patterns)
  Pass 3 — SLM Coedit (grammarly/coedit-large) contextual rewrite

Grammar categories covered:
  01. Articles (a/an)
  02. Subject-Verb Agreement — 1st person
  03. Subject-Verb Agreement — 2nd/plural
  04. Subject-Verb Agreement — 3rd singular
  05. Modal Verb + Base Form
  06. Tense Errors (did + past)
  07. Tense Errors (have/has + past participle)
  08. Passive Voice Errors
  09. Gerund vs Infinitive
  10. Preposition Errors
  11. Comparative & Superlative
  12. Double Negatives
  13. Pronoun Agreement
  14. Sentence Patterns (there is/are, it is/are)
  15. Word Order Errors
  16. Redundant Words
  17. Pleonasms / Verbose Phrases
  18. Punctuation & Spacing
  19. Contractions (missing apostrophe)
  20. Doubled Words
  21. Spelling / OCR Fixes
  22. Number Agreement
  23. Conditional Sentences
  24. Relative Clauses
  25. VLM / AV Domain-Specific

Usage:
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py                   # interactive menu
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py --txt file.txt    # text file
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py --pdf file.pdf    # PDF file
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py --text "caption"  # direct input
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py --save report.txt # save output
  python waymo_caption_checker_v2.py --no-slm          # skip SLM pass

Install SLM (optional but recommended):
  pip install transformers torch sentencepiece
"""

